Daniels Igoni, Yenagoa The General Overseer of Omega Fire Ministry, Apostle Johnson Suleman, says that the Governor of Bayelsa State, Mr Douye Diri, is “a divine gift” to the people of the state. He said the emergence of Diri as governor of Bayelsa was “the beginning of a new dawn for the state.” Suleiman said this when he paid a courtesy visit to the governor at the Government House, Yenagoa. He described Diri as a profound leader. Suleman said, “I want to tell the people of the state that it is a new dawn for them. I pray that God will give the governor ideas and plant around him the right people that will help in bringing peace and development to the state.” In his remarks, Diri described Suleman as God’s general and prayed that God would continue to uphold him.  Copyright PUNCH.
